In line with our commitment to supporting the most vulnerable in society and alleviating poverty, the City of Cape Town has provided rates rebates of more than R93,8 million to 27 989 senior citizens and people with disabilities during the 2016/17 financial year. The City has also waived R5,5 million in rates for 2 172 indigent residents. The total rates forgone in the form of rebates, exemptions and reductions amounted to over R1,2 billion in the period ending on 30 June 2017. Rates rebates and exemptions ensure that rates are affordable to residents that are most in need. All residents deserve to access opportunities regardless of their socio-economic circumstances.